                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This inscription dated in the <hi rend="bold">3rd year</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Nandippōttaraiyar</hi> may be assigned to Nandivarman III. It registers a gift of 200 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of rice for feeding 100 persons on the day of Tiruvādirai, by <hi rend="bold">Gaṇavatimāṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Pagaichchandira Viśaiaraiyaṉ</hi> of Vaḍuvūr in Mīpuḻai-nāḍu. This inscription indicates that the limits of the Pallava empire still continued to extend as far south as the Pudukkottai State.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
